<h1>Core Practices</h1>
[/et_pb_text][/et_pb_column][/et_pb_row][/et_pb_section][et_pb_section admin_label="Section" fullwidth="off" specialty="off"][et_pb_row admin_label="Row" make_fullwidth="off" use_custom_width="off" width_unit="on" use_custom_gutter="off" padding_mobile="off" allow_player_pause="off" parallax="off" parallax_method="off" make_equal="off" parallax_1="off" parallax_method_1="off" column_padding_mobile="off"][et_pb_column type="4_4"][et_pb_text admin_label="Text" background_layout="light" text_orientation="left" use_border_color="off" border_color="#ffffff" border_style="solid"]
<h4>The Pachakuti Mesa Tradition, in all its richness, is an evolving practice of inner and outer activities that restore balance and harmony to our relationship with All That Is.</h4>
[/et_pb_text][/et_pb_column][/et_pb_row][et_pb_row admin_label="Row" make_fullwidth="off" use_custom_width="off" width_unit="on" use_custom_gutter="off" padding_mobile="off" allow_player_pause="off" parallax="off" parallax_method="off" make_equal="on" parallax_1="off" parallax_method_1="off" parallax_2="off" parallax_method_2="off" column_padding_mobile="on"][et_pb_column type="1_2"][et_pb_image admin_label="Image" src="http://heartofthehealer.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/06/mesa-003-core-practices.jpg" show_in_lightbox="off" url_new_window="off" use_overlay="off" animation="fade_in" sticky="off" align="center" force_fullwidth="off" always_center_on_mobile="on" use_border_color="off" border_color="#ffffff" border_style="solid"] [/et_pb_image][/et_pb_column][et_pb_column type="1_2"][et_pb_image admin_label="Image" src="http://heartofthehealer.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/06/core-practices-3.jpg" show_in_lightbox="off" url_new_window="off" use_overlay="off" animation="fade_in" sticky="off" align="left" force_fullwidth="off" always_center_on_mobile="on" use_border_color="off" border_color="#ffffff" border_style="solid"] [/et_pb_image][/et_pb_column][/et_pb_row][et_pb_row admin_label="Row" make_fullwidth="off" use_custom_width="off" width_unit="on" use_custom_gutter="off" padding_mobile="off" custom_margin="10px||20px|" custom_margin_last_edited="on|tablet" background_color="#3a69c1" allow_player_pause="off" parallax="off" parallax_method="off" make_equal="off" parallax_1="off" parallax_method_1="off" column_padding_mobile="on" custom_padding="|||10px" custom_margin_tablet="0px||0px|" custom_padding_tablet="5px||0px|5px" custom_padding_last_edited="on|phone"][et_pb_column type="4_4"][et_pb_text admin_label="Text" background_layout="dark" text_orientation="left" use_border_color="off" border_color="#ffffff" border_style="solid" custom_padding="|||10px" custom_padding_last_edited="on|tablet" custom_padding_tablet="2px|5px|2px|10px"]
<h4>To Learn More about the Core Practices of the Pachakuti Mesa Tradition, please click on one of the links below.</h4>
[/et_pb_text][/et_pb_column][/et_pb_row][et_pb_row admin_label="Row" make_fullwidth="off" use_custom_width="off" width_unit="on" use_custom_gutter="off" padding_mobile="off" allow_player_pause="off" parallax="off" parallax_method="off" make_equal="on" parallax_1="off" parallax_method_1="off" parallax_2="off" parallax_method_2="off" parallax_3="off" parallax_method_3="off" column_padding_mobile="on"][et_pb_column type="1_3"][et_pb_blurb admin_label="Blurb" title="Creating a Basic Mesa" url="http://heartofthehealer.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/06/2016-15-PMT-Basic-Mesa.pdf" url_new_window="off" use_icon="on" font_icon="%%71%%" icon_color="#dd542a" use_circle="off" circle_color="#dd542a" use_circle_border="off" circle_border_color="#dd542a" icon_placement="top" animation="top" background_layout="light" text_orientation="center" use_icon_font_size="off" use_border_color="off" border_color="#ffffff" border_style="solid"]

The Mesa you will learn about here is a synthesis of Peruvian shamanic coastal traditions combined with southeastern Andean Paqokuna practices. The Pachakuti Mesa anchors the universe in front of you and brings the cosmos to you.

[/et_pb_blurb][/et_pb_column][et_pb_column type="1_3"][et_pb_blurb admin_label="Blurb" title="Hucha Mikhuy" url="http://heartofthehealer.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/06/2016-Hucha-Mikhuy.pdf" url_new_window="off" use_icon="on" font_icon="%%71%%" icon_color="#dd542a" use_circle="off" circle_color="#dd542a" use_circle_border="off" circle_border_color="#dd542a" icon_placement="top" animation="top" background_layout="light" text_orientation="center" use_icon_font_size="off" use_border_color="off" border_color="#ffffff" border_style="solid"]

A great practical and developmental asset to the healer is the ability to organically cleanse and transform hucha from the body. Hucha mikhuy is the process of activating the kurku k‚Äôanchay‚Äôs inborn capacity to rid itself of the density that hinders the natural expression of health and creativity.

[/et_pb_blurb][/et_pb_column][et_pb_column type="1_3"][et_pb_blurb admin_label="Blurb" title="Becoming Hampikamayoq" url="http://heartofthehealer.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/06/2016-becoming-hampikamayoq.pdf" url_new_window="off" use_icon="on" font_icon="%%71%%" icon_color="#dd542a" use_circle="off" circle_color="#dd542a" use_circle_border="off" circle_border_color="#dd542a" icon_placement="top" animation="top" background_layout="light" text_orientation="center" use_icon_font_size="off" use_border_color="off" border_color="#ffffff" border_style="solid"]

Becoming a medicine carrier means that you will have increased capacity for manifesting change in the world. Identifying some dream or vision of how you might be in service and right relationship to your family, friends, community, or the planet itself, is an important element of this work.

[/et_pb_blurb][/et_pb_column][/et_pb_row][et_pb_row admin_label="Row" make_fullwidth="off" use_custom_width="off" width_unit="on" use_custom_gutter="off" padding_mobile="off" allow_player_pause="off" parallax="off" parallax_method="off" make_equal="on" parallax_1="off" parallax_method_1="off" parallax_2="off" parallax_method_2="off" column_padding_mobile="on"][et_pb_column type="1_2"][et_pb_blurb admin_label="Blurb" title="Hampikamayoq Breathwork" url="http://heartofthehealer.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/06/2016-Hampikamayoq-Breath.pdf" url_new_window="off" use_icon="on" font_icon="%%71%%" icon_color="#dd542a" use_circle="off" circle_color="#dd542a" use_circle_border="off" circle_border_color="#dd542a" icon_placement="top" animation="top" background_layout="light" text_orientation="center" use_icon_font_size="off" use_border_color="off" border_color="#ffffff" border_style="solid"]

The purpose of Hampikamayoq breathwork is threefold: To cleanse and clear dense energy; To fortify the energy system by the deliberate intake and distribution of Kawsay; To make the healer a better carrier of spirit medicine.

[/et_pb_blurb][/et_pb_column][et_pb_column type="1_2"][et_pb_blurb admin_label="Blurb" title="Mesa Evolution" url="https://youtu.be/8bOvW7SYGE8" url_new_window="off" use_icon="on" font_icon="%%40%%" icon_color="#dd542a" use_circle="off" circle_color="#dd542a" use_circle_border="off" circle_border_color="#dd542a" icon_placement="top" animation="top" background_layout="light" text_orientation="center" use_icon_font_size="off" use_border_color="off" border_color="#ffffff" border_style="solid"]

Video by Yola Dunne - ‚ÄúI wondered how the evolution of my mesa, from the introductory class until now, would appear on video. So I played around, and came up with this. This is one way for me to express how this class (and the Pachakuti Mesa Tradition) has impacted my life.‚Äù

